<?sml-point-size 12>
<Para><?sml-need 3>Throughout the descriptions that follow, the term
<Symbol Role="Variable">object</Symbol>
indicates the directory object
whose directory entry contains the corresponding directory attributes.
</Para>
<ItemizedList>
<ListItem>
<?sml-need 5>
<Para><Literal>DS_A_AUTHORITY_REVOC_LIST</Literal>
</Para>
<Para>This attribute occurs only in entries that describe a certification
authority (CA).  It lists all the certificates issued to any of the CAs
known to this CA, and later revoked.  Each value of this OM attribute
is signed by the CA.
</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para><Literal>DS_A_CA_CERT</Literal>
</Para>
<Para>This attribute specifies the certificates assigned to the object, which is a 
CA.
</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para><Literal>DS_A_CERT_REVOC_LIST</Literal>
</Para>
<Para>This attribute occurs only in entries that describe a CA. It lists the certificates issued by this CA and later
revoked.  Each value of this OM attribute is signed by the CA.
</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para><Literal>DS_A_CROSS_CERT_PAIR</Literal>
</Para>
<Para>This attribute specifies one or two certificates held in the entry of a CA. The first certificate is that of one CA, guaranteed by
a second CA; whereas, the second certificate is that of the second CA,
guaranteed by the first CA.
</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para><Literal>DS_A_USER_CERT</Literal>
</Para>
<Para>This attribute specifies the user certificates assigned to the object,
which may be any user certificate, including a CA certificate.
</Para>
</ListItem>
</ItemizedList>
