<Sect1 Id="DCEADG.REFSAP.div.4">
<Title>OM Class Hierarchy</Title>
<Para>The remainder of this chapter defines the additional OM classes used
by SAP.
This section shows the hierarchical organization of the OM classes
that are defined in the following sections,
and it shows which OM classes inherit additional OM attributes
from their OM superclasses.
<IndexTerm Id="DCEADG.REFSAP.indx.1">
<Primary>superclasses</Primary>
<Secondary>OM</Secondary>
</IndexTerm>In the following list, subclassification is indicated by indentation, and the names of
abstract OM classes are in italics.
</Para>
<Para><Symbol Role="Variable">OM_C_OBJECT</Symbol>
</Para>
<ItemizedList>
<ListItem>
<Para><Literal>DS_C_ALGORITHM_IDENT</Literal>
</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para><Literal>DS_C_CERT_PAIR</Literal>
</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para><Symbol Role="Variable">DS_C_SIGNATURE</Symbol>
</Para>
